claim.claim-text:
A method for the reduction of inrush current to an electrical load (233) due to voltage sags (106) on an input power voltage (100), comprising the steps of:
- providing a current limiting circuit (400) comprising an selectively removable impedance coupled between the input power voltage (100) and the load (233),
- providing a sag detector (213) coupled to receive the input power voltage (100), the sag detector operative to provide a signal (223) once it detects a voltage sag (106) in the input power voltage (100) during steady state operation of the load and to alter the signal (223) once it detects that the voltage sag (106) has ended;
- providing an impedance removal timing circuit (403) coupled to receive the input power voltage (100) and a load voltage as measured across the load (233), the impedance removal timing circuit (403) operative to provide an impedance removal signal (406) in response to comparison of the input power voltage (100) and the load voltage;
- applying the input power voltage (100) to the load through the current limiting circuit (400),
- detecting a voltage sag (106) in the input power voltage (100) during steady-state operation of the electrical load (233);
- in response to the signal (223) from the sag detector (213) indicating a voltage sag, actuating the current limiting circuit (400) to add the impedance between the input power voltage (100) and the load (233);
- detecting the end of a voltage sag (106) with the sag detector (213);
- subsequent to the altered signal (223) from the sag detector (213) indicating an end of a voltage sag (106), receiving the impedance removal signal from the impedance removal timing circuit; and
- in response to the impedance removal signal (406), reconnecting the input power voltage (100) to the load (233) through the current limiting circuit (400).

An apparatus for the reduction of inrush current to an electrical load (233) due to voltage sags (106) on an input power voltage (100), comprising:
- a current limiting circuit (400) including a selectively removable impedance coupled between the input power voltage (100) and the electrical load (233);
- a sag detector (213) coupled to receive the input power voltage (100), the sag detector (213) operative to provide a signal (223) once it detects a voltage sag (106), and to alter the signal (223) once it detects that the voltage sag (106) has ended;
- an impedance removal timing circuit (403) coupled to receive the input power voltage (100) and a load voltage as measured across the load (233), the impedance removal timing circuit (403) operative to provide an impedance removal signal (406) in response to comparison of the input power voltage (100) and the load voltage;
- the current limiting circuit (400) being operative, in response to the signal (223) from the sag detector (213) indicating a voltage sag, to disconnect the input power voltage (100) from the load (233); and
- the current limiting circuit (400) being operative, in response to the altered signal from the sag detector (213) indicating that a voltage sag (106) has ended and to the impedance removal signal (406), to reconnect the input power voltage (100) to the load (233) through the current limiting circuit (400).
